<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
The type-material of the species has been collected by Paoli in moss at Lago 
<normalizedToken originalValue="PalÃ¹" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Palu</normalizedToken>
, Sondrio 1), in the mountains of North Italy, at an altitude of 1300 m; it is not present in the Berlese Collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Willmann (1925, p. 9) described the &quot; variety &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="paolianus" variety="longisetosus">longisetosus</taxonomicName>
that is also described by Sellnick &amp; Forsslund (1955, p. 509, figs. 28, 29). As long as 
<pageBreakToken pageId="70" pageNumber="71" start="start">topotypic</pageBreakToken>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paolianus" subGenus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" subGenus.innerRound="1" subGenus.outerRound="1">paolianus</taxonomicName>
are not discovered and described, the identity of the species, and its relation to the &quot; variety &quot; remain, however, uncertain.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">1) Lago Palu and Sondrio are apparently two localities, although Berlese's record makes the impression that Lago Palue is situated in the province of Sondrio.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
